On the issue of different parameter config for tests with expected results, we could just add an optional parameter to the test instance and get parameter methods. i.e.

```
    @classmethod
    def get_test_params(cls, parameter_set="default"):
```

```
    @classmethod
    def create_test_instance(cls, test_params="default"):
```

I'm not really sure what the List is used for currently, what I had in mind was just an if statement really, i.e.

```
    @classmethod
    def get_test_params(cls, parameter_set="default"):
        if parameter_set == "default": 
            return {"n_parameter_samples": 5}
        elif parameter_set == "result_comparison":
            return {"n_parameter_samples": 25}
        else:
            raise ValueError("Invalid test parameter set.")
```

Returning a dictionary could also work, like you said? i.e.

```
    @classmethod
    def get_test_params(cls):
        params = {}
        params["default"] = {"n_parameter_samples": 5}
        params["result_comparison"] = {"n_parameter_samples": 25}
        return params
```
